# 🎯 **6. Trading Implications (What Professionals Actually Do)**

## **1. Spot SGD gives clues about SORA before SORA moves**

SGD strength → expect SORA up
SGD weakness → expect SORA down

Very high edge.

---

## **2. Liquidity analysis helps forecast curve shape**

Tight liquidity → pay front-end SORA, flattener
Loose liquidity → receive front-end SORA, steepener

---

## **3. CCS basis trades are a direct play on SGD liquidity**

* Basis tightens when liquidity is scarce → pay USD/receive SGD
* Basis widens when liquidity flush → receive USD/pay SGD

---

## **4. FX swaps adjust before IRS**

So curve traders must **monitor FX swap points live**.

SGD IRS can lag significantly.

---

## **5. You can trade MAS FX stance indirectly via SGD rates**

A MAS strengthening bias → higher SORA → higher SGD IRS
A MAS easing (weaker SGD) bias → lower SORA → lower IRS

This is one of the cleanest macro trades in Singapore.

